==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perfidious
<hw>Per*fid"i*ous</hw> <pr>(p⟦etil⟧r*f⟦icr⟧d"⟦icr⟧*⟦ucr⟧s; 277)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>perfidious</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Guilty of perfidy; violating good faith or vows; false to trust or
confidence reposed; treacherous; faithless; <as>as, a
<ex>perfidious</ex> friend</as>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Involving, or characterized by, perfidy.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Involved in this <xex>perfidious</xex> fraud.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perfidiously</ent>⟦br⟧
